					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On the fifth pillar, in the inner enclosure of the Ujjīvanāthasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 13: 984 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a gift of 90 sheep for a perpetual lamp to be burnt with an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee daily in the temple of Tirukkaṟkuḍi-paramēśvara by Uḍaitalai Tirukkaṟkuḍi Naṅgai, wife of Uḻaichchāṇaṉ Kaṇḍaṉ Śāttan, a resident of Nandipanmamaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam</hi> on the southern bank.</p>						

						<p>The temple officials <hi rend="italic">(dēvakanmigaḷ)</hi> received the sheep and agreed to burn the lamp. The lady also donated one lamp stand.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 320.</p>						

						</summary>
